channel.title: Comments on: Sydney Daring Bakers Meet-up at NewsCaf

item.title: By: kim at allconsuming
item.dc:creator: kim at allconsuming
item.description:
So bummed I didn't make it (must have been a different Kim)!
Would love to know if/when it's happening again as it'd be great to meet some other food bloggers in Sydney.

item.title: By: Maria@TheGouremtChallenge
item.dc:creator: Maria@TheGouremtChallenge
item.description: wow, I would not have known those were pancakes! the topping is so generous it totally dwarfs the pancakes!! But hey if it tastes good bring it on hey?

item.title: By: Anita@noredmeat
item.dc:creator: Anita@noredmeat
item.description: That's so funny you got a berry frappe. I had a craving today for a berry frappe. Just walked down to boost juice and settled for a berry sport smoothie. Last weekend I went to Bill's for the first time and got his pancakes. Yours look just as good. So bummed I missed this meetup. Hopefully I can make the next one. Would love to meet everyone.

item.title: By: sophia
item.dc:creator: sophia
item.description: What a great meetup! I think brunch is the BEST thing to have in such events...such homey, simple, no-snobbiness comfort food!

item.title: By: Cakelaw
item.dc:creator: Cakelaw
item.description: This sounds like it was fun - and I love the look of your pancakes. I was keen to attend if I could, but I had a non-negotiable family commitment the same weekend. I'm hoping another will be organised so I can attend!
